      • readData

        public SparseMatrix readData(double binThold)
                      throws java.lang.Exception
        Read data from the data file. Note that we didn't take care of the duplicated lines.
        Parameters:
        binThold - the threshold to binarize a rating. If a rating is greater than the threshold, the value will be 1; otherwise 0. To disable this feature, i.e., keep the original rating value, set the threshold a negative value
        Returns:
        a sparse matrix storing all the relevant data
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
